# Backend Fastify Rules

- All ingest endpoints must be implemented as Fastify routes with an explicit JSON Schema on the route definition.
- The route schema is mandatory and must validate the full payload contract:
  - required `sessionId`, `sentAt`, `events`
  - strict event unions for `mouse`, `scroll`, `idle`
  - numeric constraints such as `percent <= 100`
- Never trust `request.body` shape without schema validation; invalid payloads must be rejected automatically with `4xx`.
- Keep the request path fast: acknowledge valid ingest requests immediately with HTTP `200` and a tiny JSON body such as `{"ok":true}`.
- Do not perform slow synchronous work in the request handler.
- Logging must be lightweight and structured through Fastify/Pino; avoid noisy `console.log` per event and never block the event loop with file I/O.
- If persistence is needed, enqueue or hand off work after validation; do not keep the client connection open for downstream processing.
- CORS policy must be explicit. Do not leave production ingest endpoints effectively open to every origin by accident.
- Any backend contract change must be mirrored in the SDK types in the same change.
- All operator/dashboard API endpoints must have `preHandler: [requireOperatorAuth]`. Ingest `POST /api/events` is public.
- Origin validation must use `new URL(origin).origin` for strict comparison ‚Äî never `startsWith`.
- `siteKey` is required for ingest by default. `ALLOW_INGEST_WITHOUT_SITEKEY=true` is dev-only.
- Body limit is 256 KB via Fastify `bodyLimit`. Security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`) are set via `onSend` hook.
- Never log raw tokens or full siteKeys. Pino `redact` covers `req.headers.authorization`.

## Dashboard API Routes

- `GET /api/sessions` ‚Äî list sessions with event counts. Supports `limit` (max 200) and `offset` query params.
- `GET /api/sessions/:sessionId` ‚Äî session detail with events (up to 5000). Optional `?type=` filter.
- `GET /api/events/live` ‚Äî Server-Sent Events stream. Broadcasts each batch after persistence. Keep-alive every 15s.
- `GET /api/sessions/:sessionId/conversions` ‚Äî List conversions with goal name/type.
- `GET /api/reconciliation/daily?days=30&site_id=X` ‚Äî daily Metrica-vs-SURFAI counts from `metrica_daily_reconciliation`. Populated by the `npm run metrica:reconcile` job.
- `POST /api/goals` ‚Äî Create goal (name, type, rules, is_primary). Tenant via `X-Tenant-Id` header.
- `GET /api/goals` ‚Äî List goals for tenant.
- `PUT /api/goals/:goalId` ‚Äî Update goal.
- `DELETE /api/goals/:goalId` ‚Äî Soft-delete goal.
- `POST /api/conversions` ‚Äî Server-side conversion registration (requires `sessionId` or `visitorId` + `goalId`).
- Dashboard files are served from `dashboard/` under `/dashboard/` prefix via a second `@fastify/static` registration.

## Feature Engineering Pipeline

- `server/features/extractors.js` ‚Äî modular extractors for each event type (mouse, scroll, click, form, engagement, session, context, cross_session, bot_signals).
- `server/features/store.js` ‚Äî `computeAndStore(sessionId, projectId, siteId, clientIp)` fetches all events, extracts behavioral features, runs bot scoring, merges GeoIP lookup, and upserts into `session_features`.
- `server/features/geoip.js` ‚Äî singleton MMDB reader (`dbip-city` + `asn` from `@ip-location-db`). Initialized once in `server.js` startup. `lookup(ip)` returns `{geo_country, geo_region, geo_city, geo_timezone, geo_latitude, geo_longitude, geo_asn, geo_asn_org, geo_is_datacenter, geo_is_mobile_carrier}` or all-null if not initialized.
- `server/features/backfill.js` ‚Äî batch backfill script for existing sessions (`npm run backfill`). Does NOT pass an IP ‚Äî historical sessions keep `geo_*` NULL forever.
- Features are recomputed on every batch arrival (fire-and-forget after persistence + SSE broadcast).
- `GET /api/sessions/:sessionId/features` ‚Äî returns computed ML feature vector for a session.
- Migration 004: `session_features` table with mouse dynamics, scroll behavior, click patterns, form behavior, engagement, session-level, context, and cross-session features.
- Migration 010 added extended context columns (timezone, viewport, dpr, hardware, utm, ...). Migration 011 added GeoIP columns.
- Sliding-window aggregation stored as JSONB (1s, 5s, 30s windows for mouse velocity).

## GeoIP & Client IP Handling

- The Fastify instance is configured with `trustProxy: "127.0.0.1"` so `request.ip` reflects the real client IP via `X-Forwarded-For` from the local nginx. Do NOT widen this to trust arbitrary proxies.
- The client IP is read once inside the `POST /api/events` handler as `request.ip`, passed to `computeAndStore()`, and discarded when the handler returns. It is NEVER persisted in `events`, `raw_batches`, or any other table. Only derived `geo_*` columns on `session_features` persist.
- The GeoIP module must degrade gracefully when MMDB packages are missing (local dev): log a startup warning, return all-null objects from `lookup()`, and keep the ingest path working.
- Attribution (CC BY 4.0 from DB-IP): dashboards and cabinets rendering geo data must include a visible link to `https://db-ip.com/`. TODO as of 2026-04-10.

## Yandex Metrica Enrichment (Slice 1)

- `server/features/yandex-metrica.js` ‚Äî Reports API client. Reads `YANDEX_METRICA_TOKEN` at call time, not at require time, so a missing token never blocks server boot. Errors are classified via `err.code` (`TOKEN_MISSING`, `TOKEN_INVALID`, `RATE_LIMIT`, `SERVER_ERROR`, `REQUEST_ERROR`). `accuracy=` is omitted ‚Äî `accuracy=full` requires a paid Metrica tier.
- `server/jobs/metrica-reconcile.js` ‚Äî standalone CLI worker. UPSERTs `(site_id, date)` into `metrica_daily_reconciliation`. Takes `--date`, `--site`, `--dry-run`, `--verbose`. Ignores `YANDEX_METRICA_ENABLED` for manual runs (flag only gates scheduled cron/systemd runs).
- Only sites with non-null `sites.yandex_counter_id` are in scope. Adding a new site is a one-line UPDATE.
- `metrica_goals_total` is deliberately NULL in Slice 1 ‚Äî Metrica has no "sum across all goals" metric, so per-goal totals need discovering goals via `/management/v1/counter/{id}/goals` first. Deferred to Slice 2+.
- Slice plan: `vault/decisions/2026-04-19_yandex_metrica_enrichment.md`.
